  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed across key boundary condition inputs (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, blood viscosity) using a Monte Carlo propagation of ±5% tolerances on each parameter, yielding a 95th-percentile band on the relative hemolysis index of ±0.08 RH units. A screening sensitivity study was additionally conducted to rank input contributions; results indicated that rotational speed and gap clearance were primary drivers. The structured sensitivity analysis artefact is referenced in the supplementary technical report and was used to inform mesh refinement priorities.",
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-claim-001",
